Here’s the recipe: 
 
Ingredients: 
Approx. 1.5 pounds Brussels sprouts (or other veggies of choice!) 
1/4 cup apple cider vinegar 
1/4 cup whiskey 
1/4 cup unsalted vegan butter (@floraplantus)
1/4 cup maple syrup 
1/2 handful fresh thyme
1/2 tsp sea salt 
1 pinch pepper 
1 cup water 
 
Directions:
 
In a large pan/pot, sauté the veggies in the plant butter for a few minutes. 
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil. 
Lower heat and let simmer for 10-15 minutes. Enjoy! 

#MadeWithFlora @floraplantus (it’s vegan, but tastes, looks & works just like dairy butter!). Find out where you can buy Flora on Flora.com

Videography by @adamkenworthy & @sameatsplants_ for @bestofvegan 💚🌿

Vegan Fried Sage & Browned Butter Cacio e Pepe featuring @FloraPlantUS’ plant butter:
 
(CC: watch in full screen to view closed captions)

Ingredients:
 
Serves 2
 
7.5 Spaghetti (dry weight)
3 tbsp unsalted vegan butter
1/2 tsp freshly ground pepper
3 minced garlic cloves 
1/4-1/3 cup reserved pasta water 
1/2 cup grated vegan parmesan cheese 
Sea salt to taste
1 handful fresh sage 
More vegan butter (salted) for frying 
 
 
Instructions:
 
Cook the pasta according to package instructions (reserve some of the pasta water)
Drain the pasta, then add it to a pan with the 3tbsp vegan butter. Cook over medium heat. 
Add the pepper, sea salt and grated vegan Parmesan cheese, then add a bit of pasta water, mix and cook until the butter and cheese are melted. Add a little more water if need be. 
In a separate small pan, heat the salted butter until it starts browning. Add the sage and fry until just crispy but not burnt. 
Serve with the pasta and a little more fresh pepper. 

Video by @AdamKenworthy for @BestOfVegan using @FloraPlantUS plant butter. 

Go to https://www.flora.com/en-us/floraplant/find-us to find out where you can buy Flora Plant Butter.

(Closed captions provided in full-screen mode) 

Recipe: 
5-6 large yellow onions, thinly sliced
4 garlic cloves, minced 
1/4 cup unsalted vegan butter (@floraplantus)
1 handful fresh thyme 
1 bay leaf
1/4 cup vegan mozzarella 
1/2-3/4 cup white wine 
2-3 tablespoons all-purpose flour 
4 cups vegetable broth 
Sea salt and pepper to taste
 
To serve: 
Grilled sliced sourdough bread or baguette
salted vegan butter (@floraplantus)
 
Instructions: 
 
Add the vegan butter to a pot with the thinly sliced onions and caramelize them over medium heat for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to low-medium and caramelize for another 10-15 minutes (stir to prevent burning).
Each time it starts browning, deglaze with a little white wine (1/2-3/4 cup total). 
Once the onions are fully caramelized, add the garlic and all-purpose flour and mix again. 
Add the thyme, bay leaf and broth, cover and let simmer over low to medium heat for 10-12 minutes.
Remove the thyme and bay leaf and then add salt and pepper to taste. 
Add the butter to the bread, top with vegan mozzarella and broil. Serve with the soup.

Ingredients: 

(Makes 12-15 cookies)

INGREDIENTS 
1/2 cup unsalted @FloraPlantUS plant butter (112g)
1/2 cup brown sugar
1/2 cup cane sugar 
1 + 1/4 cup all purpose flour* 153g (note: spoon the flour into the measuring cup or use a scale) 
1/4 cup cacao powder
1 tsp baking Soda
1 pinch of sea salt
2 Tbsp unsweetened cashew milk (or any other non-dairy milk)
3.5 oz dark chocolate (roughly chopped)
1/2 tsp sea salt flakes 

INSTRUCTIONS

1) Preheat the oven to 350°F
2) Cream the plant butter and sugar in a bowl using a (preferably electric) mixer. 
3) Sift the all-purpose flour, then add the cacao powder, baking soda and sea salt. 
4) Mix using a spatula or your hands, add the cashew milk and mix again.
5) Roughly chop the chocolate and mix 1/2 of it into the dough. 
6) Form 12-15 small dough balls and place them on a thin baking tray/cookie sheet lined with parchment paper (you may need 2 trays if you don’t have a large one). Make sure you leave enough space between the cookies as they’ll spread while baking.
7) Bake for 10 minutes slightly above the middle of the oven (if you made bigger cookies or if you’re using a glass or other thicker tray, you may need to increase the baking time by 1-2 minutes, but be sure to still check at the 10-minute mark).
8) Add the remaining chopped chocolate to each of the cookies and sprinkle the sea salt flakes on top. 
9) Let the cookies cool for at least 10-20 minutes, then enjoy with a glass of ice cold plant milk!

Served with vegan ranch dressing! Get both recipes below ⬇️

A huge thank you to @AlexaJenal for taking over Best of Vegan today and to @FlamingoInterpreting for providing the voiceover for this video 🧡

Vegan Ranch dressing by @AlexaJenal:

1 cup vegan Mayo 
2 tbsp plant milk
2 tsp Apple cider vinegar
1 tsp onion powder
1/4 tsp salt n pepper
1 tbsp dill, chives and parsley

Buffalo Cauliflower Wings:
Ingredients
Ingredients:

1 cauliflower head, cut into florets
Batter ingredients:

Dry: 
1 cup all-purpose flour 
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp paprika 
1 tsp onion powder 
½ tsp ground pepper
½ tsp sea salt 

Wet:
¾ cup unsweetened plant milk
⅓ cup water 

Buffalo sauce ingredients:

2 tbsp soy sauce
2 tbsp hot sauce 
2 tbsp maple syrup
2 tbsp cornstarch
¼ cup water 
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar 
2 tbsp vegan butter

Instructions

Preheat the oven to 400°F/200°C. 
Prepare the batter by mixing the dry ingredients in a bowl and slowly pouring and mixing in the wet ingredients using a whisk or a fork until you get a smooth, lump-free consistency. 
Line a large baking tray with parchment paper and start dipping the cauliflower florets in the batter until they’re fully coated. Shake the florets lightly to remove any excess batter and then place them on the baking tray one by one. 
Bake for 25 minutes (optional: flip half way through). 
While the florets are baking, start making the sauce by melting the vegan butter in a small pot. Once it’s melted add all other ingredients. Mix and cook it until it starts to thicken. 
Take the florets out of the oven and lower the heat to 350F. Dip each floret into the sauce, remove any excess and then place it back on the baking tray.
Bake for 25 more minutes and then let the cauliflower wings cool for a few minutes (but not too long, they’re best eaten warm to hot). 
Serve with vegan ranch dressing and enjoy!

Full recipe below ⬇️ Check out Lloyd’s new eBook at plantcrazii.com or via the link in his bio @plantcrazii 🧡

Recipe: 

You will need: 
1 large cauliflower 
2 tbsp hot sauce 
1/2 tsp black pepper 
1 tsp all purpose seasoning salt Oil for deep frying(vegetable oil, avocado oil, sunflower oil) 

Wet mix Bowl:
1 1/2 cup dairy free milk 
2 tbsp white vinegar 

Dry Mix Bowl:
1 cup all purpose flour
1/2 cup corn starch 
3 tsp all purpose seasoning salt 
3 tsp black pepper 
1/2 tsp cayenne pepper 
1 tsp onion powder 
1 tsp garlic powder 
1/2 tbsp paprika 
1/2 tbsp dry crushed rosemary 

Method: 
Rinse cauliflower and seperate into florets 
Coat florets with 2tbsp hot sauce, 1/2 tsp black pepper and 1 tsp seasoning salt 
Mix the ingredients of the wet bowl mix together 
Mix the ingredients of the dry bowl mix together 
Dip florets into the dry mix then the wet mix and again into the dry mix. 
Deep fry florets in hot oil for 10 minutes or until golden and crunchy.

Recipe & video by @plantcrazii

Ingredients:

•2 cups cubed watermelon
•2 whole limes – squeezed of all juice
•2 whole stalks scallion – sliced
•1 jalapeño – minced
•handful of fresh coriander – roughly chopped plus whole leaves for garnish
•1/2 English cucumber – diced same size as watermelon
•zest from 1 lime
•2-3 tbsp good extra virgin olive oil
•kosher salt
•freshly ground black pepper
•4 flour tortillas
•cooking spray

1. Place watermelon in a large bowl. Add in fresh lime juice, mix, and let sit for at least 15-20 minutes. This allows the lime juice to absorb into the watermelon, break it down a bit, and balance out the sweetness.
2. Make the tortillas. In a nonstick skillet, spray with cooking spray and place over medium high flame. Once hot, add in the tortilla. It’ll start forming bubbles, so just use your knife to carefully poke a few holes so it flattens. Toast on each side for about 1-2 minutes until golden brown. Remove and cut into chips. Set aside to cool.
3. In a separate large shallow bowl, mix together scallions, jalapeños, coriander, cucumber, lime zest, black pepper, a large pinch of kosher salt and olive oil.
4. Add watermelon to the cucumber mixture, straining from the remaining lime juice mixture. Combine well, taste to make sure there is enough salt. Garnish with fresh coriander leaves. Serve with homemade chippers!

[Recipe & Videography by @ChefPriyanka, as posted on https://www.chefpriyanka.com/watermelon-ceviche/]

Follow @ChefPriyanka for even more delicious recipes!

How to make @AddictedToHumus’ Super Crunchy Wedges🍟

Ingredients:
- 750g potatoes, into wedges
- 1/2 cup bread crumbs
- 2 tbsp olive oil
- 1 tsp salt 
- 1/2 tsp onion powder
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1/2 tsp paprika powder
.
1. Preheat the oven to 200°C/400F
2. In a bowl mix potato wedges with olive oil and spices until well covered
3. Add bread crumbs and combine well
4. Spread out on a baking tray and sprinkle with some more oil
5. Bake for 45 minutes until golden brown
6. Enjoy with some homemade ketchup.

VEGAN MATCHA BONBONS by @DatesAndAvocados 💚

INGREDIENTS (for 30 bonbons)
3/4 cup raw cacao butter, melted
1/4 cup + 2 Tbsp raw cashew butter
3 Tbsp maple syrup 
1 tsp matcha powder (ceremonial grade) 
1/2 tsp pure vanilla extract
1/4 tsp pink Himalayan salt

METHOD:
1. Start melting the cacao butter in a double boiler. If you have a thermometer, make sure you don’t heat it over 42C/108F to keep its properties.
2. Allow the melted cacao to cool down a bit before mixing it with the rest of the ingredients. It’s important to have all the ingredients at room temperature before combining them to avoid the separation of the butter.
3. In the jar of your blender combine the cashew butter, maple syrup, vanilla extract, salt and cacao butter and blend until you get a smooth mixture. It won’t take more than 30 seconds.
4. Add the matcha powder at last and blend again for a few more seconds until fully incorporated.
5. Fill the molds with the chocolate mixture and tap them a few times on the table to remove any air bubbles.
6. Store them in the fridge for at least 1 hour until set.
7. Once harden, you just need to pop the bonbons out of the molds.
8. They keep in the fridge for weeks, but after you try them I bet they’re going to disappear in two days!
Note:
- You can use either silicone or polycarbonate molds.

[Recipe & Photography by Lorena Salas, @datesandavocados]

Vegan Strawberry Cake by @plant.well 🍰

INGREDIENTS
1 Ib Fresh Strawberries
2 1/2 Cups All-Purpose Flour
1 1/4 Cup Sugar
1/2 Cup Plant Milk
1 1/2 Tsp Apple Cider Vinegar
1/2 Cup Dairy Free Yogurt, plain
3/4 Cup Vegan Butter Sticks, room temp
1/4 Cup Vegetable Oil
2 Tsp Vanilla
2 Tsp Baking Powder
1/2 Tsp Baking Soda
1/2 Tsp Salt
Vegan Red Food Dye (optional)

VEGAN STRAWBERRY FROSTING

1 Cup Freeze Dried Strawberries
1 Cup Vegan Butter, room temp
3-3 1/2 Cups Powdered Sugar
1 Tsp Vanilla
2-4 Tbsp plant Milk as needed to thin

INSTRUCTIONS
To make your strawberry puree, wash your berries and cut off the stems and leaves. Blend the berries until smooth and then tap through a strainer.
Add to a saucepan over low/medium heat and bring to a simmer, cook for 25-30min, stirring often, until you have 1/2 cup of reduced puree. Pour into a glass dish & place on a hot pad in the fridge until cooled to at least room temp.
Preheat your oven to 350F, spray two 9 inch circle pans with non-sticky spray, add a circle of parchment paper to the bottoms & a light dusting a flour all around.
Mix together plant milk & apple cider vinegar and set aside, this will become your "buttermilk".
In a bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda & salt, set aside.
In another bowl, mix together the butter & sugar until creamy, then add the oil, yogurt & vanilla and mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients & buttermilk in alternating increments (about 1/3 each time), mixing between each until incorporated, until everything is mixed together.
Add cooled strawberry puree and any dye if using to desired color, & mix until incorporated.
Pour evenly into both cake pans and spread out. Bake for 24-27 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean, let cool in the pan for 10 min & then transfer to a cooling rack to fully cool.
To make the frosting, cream together the butter, vanilla & milk. Add the powdered sugar in increments, mixing in between.
Blend the freeze dried strawberries and mix in.
That's it! Frost & decorate as desired!
[Recipe & Photography by @plant.well]

Vegan Banh Xeo / Savory Vietnamese Crepe by @FoodPassionical 💛

Prep time: 15 minutes
Cook time: 15 minutes
(6-8 crepes)
Batter ingredients: 
2 cups (270g) rice flour 
2 tbsp. tapioca starch 
1/4 tsp turmeric 
1/2 tsp salt 
2 cups (480ml) coconut milk
1/4 cup water as needed, if batter is too thick 

Fillings:
Lettuce
400g pan fried tofu 
1/2 cup purple cabbage, thinly sliced 
1/2 cup mung bean sprout
Handful fresh cilantro 
1 onions, sliced 
1 Cucumber, thinly sliced 
2 tbsp. chopped scallions 

Nuoc cham: 
1/4 cup (60ml) soy sauce 
1/4 cup (60ml) vegan “fish” sauce 
1/4 cup (55g) brown sugar 
1/4 cup lime juice (2-3 lime)

Method: 
1.) Mix together the batter ingredients and keep in the refrigerator for an hour (Add water if the batter if it is too thick) 
2.) In a small bowl mix together the dipping sauce ingredients and keep in refrigerator. 
3.) Heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan and add in the onion. Sauté till slightly browned. 
4.) Pour the batter then tilt and rotate the pan so the batter is evenly spread. Lower the heat to medium before adding in the fillings ingredients. 
5.) Cook till the edges is slightly crispy, then fold in half and cook for a minute or two. 
6.) Turn off the heat and transfer to a plate and serve with fresh lettuce, mint leaf, fresh cilantro and dipping sauce. Enjoy!

Sheet Pan Orange-Glazed Tofu with Roasted Veggies by @cookingforpeanuts 🧡

Serves 4

Ingredients:
1 pound Yukon Gold or red-skinned potatoes
1 ½ cups sliced red onion (about 1 medium)
1 pound green beans, ends trimmed
2 tablespoons olive oil
Salt & freshly ground black pepper to taste
4 tablespoons plus 1 ½ teaspoons peach or apricot preserves or jam
1 tablespoon plus 1 ½ teaspoons reduced-sodium soy sauce or tamari
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 large orange
1 14-ounce packet extra-firm tofu, pressed and drained

Place the potatoes into a medium saucepan with enough cold water to cover by 2 inches. Bring the water to a gentle boil and cook the potatoes for about 10 minutes, or until just fork tender. When cool to touch, Slice the potatoes in half lengthwise.

Preheat the oven to 425ºF. 

Place the green beans, red onion, and cut potatoes onto a large, rimmed nonstick baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil. Add salt and black pepper and toss until all the vegetables are evenly coated with the oil. 

Add the preserves, soy sauce, and garlic to a medium bowl. Use a microplane or fine grater and remove ¾ teaspoon orange zest. Add this to the bowl along with 3 tablespoons orange juice. Mix.

Cut the tofu widthwise into 8 equal rectangles. Cut each rectangle in half, for a total of 16 squares. Brush one side of the squares generously with the sauce using a pastry brush. Place the tofu onto the baking sheet, sauce side up. Roast for 15 minutes.

Flip the tofu squares over. Brush the other sides generously with the sauce. Roast for about 15 minutes more, or until the potatoes are cooked and the tofu is slightly crispy.

Remove from the oven and brush the tofu one more time on both sides. Add some of the sauce to the veggies if desired.

Lentil Sloppy Fries by @thevegansara 💚

What you need: 1 cup dried French green lentils rinsed, 1 Tbsp non dairy butter, 1 Tbsp neutral oil, 1 med red bell pepper minced, 1 med yellow onion minced, 3 cloves of garlic minced, 2 Tbsp tomato paste, 1/4 cup ketchup, 8 oz tomato sauce, 1/2-1 cup water, 1 tbl organic brown sugar, 2 tsp chili powder & Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 tsp red pepper flakes, kosher salt/ pepper

To make lentils: cook like pasta, with lots of salted water, bring lentils to a boil, & simmer till tender 20-30 min, drain, set aside

On stovetop over med heat,  in a large Dutch oven or pot, melt butter & heat oil over med, when hot add pepper & onion. Cook 3-5 min till soft

Add garlic & tomato paste, cook stirring till paste is caramelized & turns a deep red 2-3 min. Mix in lentils to coat

Add the remaining ingredients, & 1/2- 1 cup water, & be sure to get up any brown bits from the bottom of pot. Bring to a boil, then simmer 15-20 min for flavors to meld & sauce to thicken 

Serving Ideas: Devour on a bun with your favorite toppings or load it on some nachos, potatoes, or fries.
